                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=eerhardt",
                        "name": "eerhardt",
                        "key": "eerhardt",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=eerhardt&avatarId=37925",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=eerhardt&avatarId=37925",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=eerhardt&avatarId=37925",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=eerhardt&avatarId=37925"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Eric Erhardt",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/North_Dakota/New_Salem"
                    },
                    "body": "One option would be to add an extension point into the reader/writer where a compression library could be \"plugged in\". That way the core Arrow library doesn't need to depend on all the different compression libraries, especially when they might not be used.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=eerhardt",
                        "name": "eerhardt",
                        "key": "eerhardt",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=eerhardt&avatarId=37925",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=eerhardt&avatarId=37925",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=eerhardt&avatarId=37925",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=eerhardt&avatarId=37925"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Eric Erhardt",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/North_Dakota/New_Salem"
                    },
                    "created": "2022-06-28T15:24:12.754+0000",
                    "updated": "2022-06-28T15:24:12.754+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13468875/comment/17563043",
                    "id": "17563043",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rishabhrana",
                        "name": "rishabhrana",
                        "key": "JIRAUSER290043",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Rishabh Rana",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "[~eerhardt] I looked at the possible options and the least intrusive one I could find is exposing an interface to the user for the library. They must write a \"Decode\" class based on that interface and pass that to the reader. This way users can use any library they want to decode the body.\u00a0\r\n\r\nexample:\r\n{code:java}\r\ninterface Decoder {\r\n  public void Lz4Decode(Stream input, Stream output);\r\n  public void ZstdDecode(Stream input, Stream output);\r\n}\r\n\r\n// usage\r\npublic class LZ4Decoder: Decoder {\r\n  public void Lz4Decode(Stream input, Stream output) {\r\n    LZ4Stream.Decode(input).CopyTo(output);\r\n  }\r\n public void Lz4Decode(Stream input, Stream output) {\r\n    throw new NotImplementedException();\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\nArrowStreamReader(stream, new LZ4Decoder());\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nDoes this sound good to you?\r\n\r\nApologies for confirming again but this would impact quite a bit of code, So I wanted to make sure that I follow the best practices. Thanks!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rishabhrana",
                        "name": "rishabhrana",
                        "key": "JIRAUSER290043",
