                        "displayName": "Adam Reeve",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "Hi [~rishabhrana], I wanted to get some proof-of-concept code working using decompression so I've implemented basic Zstd decompression support in my Arrow fork: [https://github.com/apache/arrow/compare/master...adamreeve:arrow:dotnet_decompression]\r\n\r\nIt isn't in a state suitable for a pull request and just adds ZstdNet as a dependency of Apache.Arrow, which required bumping the target framework to netstandard2.0, but it might still be useful to you as a starting point, depending on how far you've already got with this.",
